Text.Value: Oh. Bye then.
Perhaps Cora can look after you, too?
His name is Jacek, he's a super brave knight.
Has it happened to you, too? I'm sorry. It's the worst.
I said leave me alone!
Your dad sounds like a good man.
First dad, now Cora...
She's really nice, but... I miss dad.
Leave me alone.
I'm sorry. It's not easy to lose someone you love.
The lady over there. She smells of lavender and roses. She's really nice.
*There's a sadness in her voice that betrays a wisdom beyond her years - she knows her father's not coming back.*
Who's Cora?
Have you seen him? Have you seen my dad?
We came here together, but he had to leave. He said that Cora would look after me.
I'm not stupid, but but - you didn't have to be so mean!
Cora's the best.
You know he's dead, right?
She's helping me write down all of my dad's stories so everyone will know how brave he is.
He is. I miss him. But I'm glad he left me with Cora. She's really nice.
Sorry kid, not today.
Dad will be so proud of me.
I've been telling Cora everything me and dad did. We're going to write the best book ever.
I don't think so...
What use are city walls if the people within them must still live in fear...?
Thank you for helping Cora. I couldn't do any of this without her.
She looks after all the kids who've got nowhere to go.
Has Cora been looking after you like your dad said?
Who's your dad?

Synopsis: Dialog with an orphan child in care of both Highberry's.
